          p Southernmost point of India, Land of the Sunrise
          .panel.panel-primary
            .panel-heading
              h2.panel-title About Kanyakumari
            .panel-body
              p Kanyakumari, located at the southern tip of India, is a famous tourist destination known for its breathtaking sunrise and sunset views over the waters. It is also a cultural hub, blending history, spirituality, and natural beauty.
              p Major attractions include the Vivekananda Rock Memorial, Thiruvalluvar Statue, and the pristine Kanyakumari Beach, making it a perfect spot for sightseeing, spiritual reflection, and relaxation.

          // Add images of Kanyakumari here
          .row.images
            .col-xs-12
              h3(style="font-size: 24px;") Vivekananda Rock Memorial
              img(src='/images/Vivekananda-Rock-Memorial.jpg', alt='Vivekananda Rock Memorial', style='width:100%; height:auto;')
              p(style="font-size: 18px;") The Vivekananda Rock Memorial stands on a small island, a serene place for meditation and reflection. It's known for its spiritual significance and panoramic ocean views.

            .col-xs-12
              h3(style="font-size: 24px;") Thiruvalluvar Statue
              img(src='/images/Thiruvalluvar-Statue.jpg', alt='Thiruvalluvar Statue', style='width:100%; height:auto;')
              p(style="font-size: 18px;") The iconic Thiruvalluvar Statue, standing 133 feet tall, honors the famous Tamil poet and philosopher. Visitors can reach the statue by boat and enjoy the scenic views of the Indian Ocean.

            // New image 1
            .col-xs-12
              h3(style="font-size: 24px;") Kanyakumari Beach
              img(src='/images/Kanyakumari-Beach.jpg', alt='Kanyakumari Beach', style='width:100%; height:auto;')
              p(style="font-size: 18px;") Kanyakumari Beach is renowned for its stunning views of both sunrise and sunset. The beach is a peaceful escape, perfect for a relaxing stroll along the shores.

            // New image 2
            .col-xs-12
              h3(style="font-size: 24px;") Manimuthar Waterfalls
              img(src='/images/Manimuthar-Waterfalls.jpg', alt='Manimuthar Waterfalls', style='width:100%; height:auto;')
              p(style="font-size: 18px;") Our Lady of Ransom Church is a beautiful white Gothic-style structure located near the shore. It's a serene place of worship, offering peace and solace to visitors.

            // New image 3
            .col-xs-12
              h3(style="font-size: 24px;") Padmanabhapuram Palace
              img(src='/images/Padmanabhapurampalace.jpg', alt='Padmanabhapuram Palace', style='width:100%; height:auto;')
              p(style="font-size: 18px;") The Padmanabhapuram Palace is a stunning example of traditional Kerala architecture, showcasing intricate woodwork, murals, and artifacts from a bygone era.

            // New image 4
            .col-xs-12
              h3(style="font-size: 24px;")  Courtallam Waterfalls
              img(src='/images/Courtallam-Waterfalls.jpg', alt=' Courtallam Waterfalls', style='width:100%; height:auto;')
              p(style="font-size: 18px;") The Tsunami Memorial stands as a tribute to those who lost their lives during the 2004 tsunami. The monument is both a place of remembrance and a spot to reflect on the strength of nature.

